{
  "answer": "**Āṅgirasa Smṛti, Chapter 1**\n\nThe lotus-born creator (Brahmā) placed all the divine śrāddha-vegetables on one scale-pan and the jackfruit (*panasa*) on the other, weighed them with his hand, and found the jackfruit slightly heavier.[^1] On that same balance, the eggplant (*bṛhatī*) was established as equal to three hundred, ginger (*ārdraka*) to six hundred, and sesame (*tila*) to one hundred—thus establishing this trio from that day forward as equal to a thousand vegetables for the satisfaction of the ancestors.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, [Chapter 1, paragraphs p-4fe9a6 and p-97de7d](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-4fe9a6).\n\n[^2]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, [Chapter 1, paragraphs p-675fe0 and p-104051](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-675fe0).",
